The paper focuses on combinatorial properties of non-planar graphs and their topological representations, which are topics commonly studied in discrete mathematics (cs.DM) and computational geometry (cs.CG). The paper also discusses the size of complete and complete bipartite graphs in these non-planar graph classes, which falls under the category of graph theory (cs.GT). The technique presented in the paper involves generating and analyzing large sets of graphs, which could be considered a problem in data structures (cs.DS) or algorithms (cs.SI).
